\ ---- dgemm-nn: A * B, no transposes -------------------------

\ basic 2x3 * 3x2 -> 2x2
1 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix [ 7 8 9 10 11 12 ] 3 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ dot product: 1x3 * 3x1 -> 1x1
1 [ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix [ 4 5 6 ] 3 1 matrix 0 1 1 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ outer product: 3x1 * 1x3 -> 3x3
1 [ 1 2 3 ] 3 1 matrix [ 4 5 6 ] 1 3 matrix 0 3 3 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ square: 2x2 * 2x2
1 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 5 6 7 8 ] 2 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ A * I = A
1 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 identity-matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ I * A = A
1 2 identity-matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ ---- alpha and beta variations -----------------------------

\ alpha=0 -> result is beta * C
0 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 5 6 7 8 ] 2 2 matrix 1 [ 100 200 300 400 ] 2 2 matrix dgemm-nn .

\ beta=0 -> result is alpha * A * B
3 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 identity-matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn .

\ alpha=2, beta=-1: 2 * A * I - C
2 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 identity-matrix -1 [ 1 1 1 1 ] 2 2 matrix dgemm-nn .

\ alpha=0, beta=0 -> zero result regardless of A, B, C
0 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 5 6 7 8 ] 2 2 matrix 0 [ 99 99 99 99 ] 2 2 matrix dgemm-nn .

\ ---- dgemm-tn: A^T * B -------------------------------------

\ A^T * A for A = [[1,2],[3,4]] -> [[10,14],[14,20]]
1 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-tn .

\ A is 3x2, A^T is 2x3, B is 3x2 -> result 2x2
1 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 3 2 matrix [ 7 8 9 10 11 12 ] 3 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-tn .

\ ---- dgemm-nt: A * B^T -------------------------------------

\ A is 2x3, B is 2x3, B^T is 3x2 -> result 2x2
1 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nt .

\ ---- dgemm-tt: A^T * B^T -----------------------------------

\ A is 2x3 -> A^T is 3x2; B is 3x2 -> B^T is 2x3; product is 3x3
1 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix [ 7 8 9 10 11 12 ] 3 2 matrix 0 3 3 0-matrix dgemm-tt .

\ ---- failure: inner dimension mismatch ---------------------

\ A 2x3 * B 2x2: A's cols (3) != B's rows (2)
1 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix [ 7 8 9 10 ] 2 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn

\ same shapes, but with -tn: A^T is 3x2, cols 2, vs B's rows 2 -- this DOES match;
\ try one that genuinely fails: A 2x3, B 3x3, -tn means A^T is 3x2, cols 2 vs B rows 3 -- mismatch
1 [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 ] 3 3 matrix 0 2 3 0-matrix dgemm-tn

\ ---- failure: C wrong shape --------------------------------

\ A*B should be 1x1 but C is 3x3
1 [ 1 2 ] 1 2 matrix [ 3 4 ] 2 1 matrix 0 3 3 0-matrix dgemm-nn

\ ---- failure: wrong types ----------------------------------

\ alpha is a string
"hi" [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn

\ A is a number
1 99 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 0 2 2 0-matrix dgemm-nn

\ C is a string
1 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 0 "C" dgemm-nn
